FBIS4-60270 "drnes100dd_94003" FBIS-NES-94-100 Daily Report 23 May 1994 Palestinian Affairs Al-Tibi: PNC To Revoke Anti-Israel Clauses Al-Tibi: PNC To Revoke Anti-Israel Clauses TA2305194494 Tel Aviv IDF Radio in Hebrew 1930 GMT 23 May 94 TA2305194494 Tel Aviv IDF Radio Hebrew BFN [Text] Dr. Ahmad al-Tibi, Yasir 'Arafat's adviser, said tonight that the next Palestine National Council [PNC] convention will revoke Palestinian Covenant clauses contravening the Oslo agreement, including those calling for Israel's annihilation. He announced that the PNC will convene soon, and for the first time in six years, the convention will be held in the Gaza Strip. Dr. al-Tibi stressed that his remarks were made with PLO chief Yasir 'Arafat's knowledge.
